<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-10100] groovyc infers the wrong type when using a method reference of a function with varargs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10100</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have the following program&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; java.util.function.Function;

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Foo&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; T method(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;... args) {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;;
    }
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Bar {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;T &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Number&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt; void test(T a) {
        Foo&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; x = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Foo&amp;lt;&amp;gt;();
        Function&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;[], T&amp;gt; b = x::method;
        T y = b.apply(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;[] {&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;str&quot;&lt;/span&gt;});
    }
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Main {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; void main(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;[] args) {
    Bar.test(1);
  }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;ActualBehaviour&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Actual Behaviour&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
org.codehaus.groovy.control.MultipleCompilationErrorsException: startup failed:
groovy4.groovy: 14: [Static type checking] - Cannot assign value of type java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;[] to variable of type T
 @ line 14, column 15.
           T y = b.apply(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;[] {&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;str&quot;&lt;/span&gt;});
                 ^1 error

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;ExpectedBehaviour&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Expected Behaviour&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Compile successfully&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that if I remove the `extends` from the parameterized function, the code compiles as expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tested against master &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/9961a67db31f7889cfb9a927ccc26c3ece0e41b9&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/9961a67db31f7889cfb9a927ccc26c3ece0e41b9&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
